article.headline: Rutgers 55, New Hampshire 48
article.story: PISCATAWAY, N.J. (AP) -- Marquis Webb came off the bench to score 14 points to lead Rutgers to a 55-48 win over New Hampshire on Wednesday night. Anthony Farmer added a season-high 12 points and three assists for the Scarlet Knights (3-5), who won their second straight game. Mike Christensen led New Hampshire (1-7) with a game-high 22 points -- on 7-of-12 shooting -- and eight rebounds, while Blagoj Janev added 10 points. Rutgers was in command for most of the game, jumping out to a 16-4 lead and holding double-digit leads for most of the game. And despite shooting just 36 percent from the floor, their defense had a strong showing and forced 15 New Hampshire turnovers. The Scarlet Knights led 37-16 at the break, but New Hampshire tried to rally with a 13-4 run to start the second half, cutting the lead to 43-34. However, the Wildcats could not get any closer as the Rutgers defense tightened.
